<p>2.1 Cookie</p>
<p>To keep the website running smoothly, we sometimes store small data files called Cookie on your computer or mobile device. A Cookie refers to a plain text file that the web server stores on a computer or mobile device. The content of a Cookie can only be retrieved or read by the server creating it. Each cookie is unique to your web browser or mobile app. Cookie usually contains an identifier, a site name, and some numbers and characters. By virtue of Cookies, a website can store such data as user preference, items in the shopping basket, etc.</p>
<p>Like most websites or Internet service providers, puppyrobot uses Cookies to improve user experience. Websites can remember the single page view (by using session Cookie) or multiple page views (by using permanent Cookie) of users. With Cookie, websites can save settings, e.g. the language, font size of a computer or mobile device, and other browsing preferences of the user. This means that users do not have to reconfigure user preferences every time they visit. If a website does not use Cookies, it will treat the user as a new visitor each time he/she opens the web page. For example, if a user logs in to a website and then goes to another web page, the user cannot be recognized by the website and will be logged out.</p>
<p>puppyrobot does not use Cookies for any purposes other than those stated in the Policy. You can manage or delete Cookies based on your own preferences. For more information, please refer to AboutCookies.org. You may clear all Cookies saved on your computer, and most web browsers offer the function to block Cookies. However, if you block Cookies, you will have to change the user settings by yourself each time you visit our website.</p>
<p>2.2 Web Beacons and Pixel Tags</P>
